----building and running the container----
1) generate a certificate/key pair first (if not using the ones in this folder); make sure their names match those in the dockerfile
2) use docker build -t quic-multiserv .
3) run the container:
docker run -it -p 127.0.0.1:12345:12345/udp quic-multiserv
alternatively modify the entrypoint:
docker run -it -p 127.0.0.1:12345:12345/udp -p 127.0.0.1:27016:27016/udp --entrypoint="cli -c /src/certs/cert.pem -k /src/certs/key.pem 127.0.0.1 27016" quic-multiserv


----actually querying stuff with a QUIC client----
i managed to build the lsquic http client after much trouble.
best follow the readme to build the boringssl libraries,
BUT then you need to build stuff manually

0) install libevent-ssl

1) install go

2) set your cwd to the lsquic repo

git clone https://github.com/litespeedtech/lsquic.git
cd lsquic

2) make boringssl:
git clone --depth=1 https://github.com/google/boringssl.git
cd boringssl
cmake .
make

3) go back to lsquic and make the example stuff
cd ..
#this assumes you are now in the lsquic repo root
git submodule update --init
cmake -DLIBSSL_DIR= ./boringssl
make